1
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:41,233
<i>I'm so close to the woman
I love, but I can't love her.</i>

2
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:44,200
<i>All those years,
you stayed with Mom.</i>

3
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> Let's be honest.</i>

4
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:47,767
<i> It's hard to love you.</i>

5
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,500
<i>So that's how it feels
when your own child hurts you.</i>

6
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,200
<i> It doesn't hurt physically.</i>

7
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,433
<i> It hurts here.</i>

8
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:56,933
<i>I need to find a way to regain
control of Jessica.</i>

9
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:58,100
<i> Mom, what do you want?</i>

10
00:00:58,233 --> 00:01:00,333
<i>Those are the videos
from the spy camera.</i>

11
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:03,233
<i> She's too meddlesome.</i>

12
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:04,567
<i>She's not even part of
the family,</i>

13
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:05,867
<i>but she keeps getting involved.</i>

14
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,733
<i>Don't let Felma and Manuel
get back together.</i>

15
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:11,700
<i>Because if that happens,
you'll be left out.</i>

16
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:14,133
<i>Enjoy your little
moments with my dad.</i>

17
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:15,633
<i> What do you mean?</i>

18
00:01:15,767 --> 00:01:18,900
<i>Ma'am Daisy just picked her up.</i>

19
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:21,533
<i>She didn't tell me
she'll pick her up.</i>

20
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:23,700
<i>Why isn't she
answering the phone?</i>

21
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,400
<i>Tetay is not picking up
the phone.</i>

22
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:27,967
<i> Jessica found an apartment.</i>

23
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,267
<i> Perhaps you're right.</i>

24
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,600
<i> You need to move out.</i>

25
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:33,000
<i>To put an end to all this mess.</i>

26
00:01:33,133 --> 00:01:34,767
<i>I'll have my marriage with
Hazel annulled,</i>

27
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:36,633
<i>and then I'll come back to you.</i>

28
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:39,933
<i>You were the one I loved before,
and you're the one I love now.</i>

29
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:42,433
<i>You are the one I will love
for the rest of my life.</i>

30
00:01:47,467 --> 00:01:52,033
And I will do everything
for us to get back together.

31
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:53,967
We had an agreement.

32
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,700
We'll be friends and that's it.

33
00:01:57,267 --> 00:01:58,667
Felma, please.

34
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,300
Let's not waste what we've had.

35
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:07,267
Let's finish what we started.

36
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,800
Let's get on with it.

37
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:10,767
Just the two of us.

38
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:11,733
Right?

39
00:02:11,867 --> 00:02:14,067
Felma, just the two
of us till the end.

40
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,500
Manuel.

41
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:30,767
Felma, I will fight for this.

42
00:02:33,133 --> 00:02:36,400
Even if it hurts so much,
even if it's hard.

43
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,667
Felma, I won't give up on us.

44
00:03:24,533 --> 00:03:25,300
Daisy?

45
00:03:27,267 --> 00:03:28,100
Daisy?

46
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:31,000
Tetay?

47
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,500
Daisy?

48
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:35,300
Tetay?

49
00:03:38,433 --> 00:03:39,767
Daisy?

50
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:43,300
Tetay, sweetie?

51
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:48,800
Daisy?

52
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,900
Tetay, sweetie?

53
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:53,200
Mon, have you seen
Daisy and Tetay?

54
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,367
Jeff, you're still here.

55
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:57,067
I saw Daisy earlier.

56
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,733
She has luggage with her.

57
00:03:58,867 --> 00:03:59,533
Where did they go?

58
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:00,733
They got in a van.

59
00:04:02,933 --> 00:04:04,067
They left.

60
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,533
No.

61
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:50,467
We can't do this.

62
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,000
This is wrong.

63
00:04:52,133 --> 00:04:54,200
This is wrong.

64
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:57,967
How long are we going to hide
what we feel for each other?

65
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,800
We're not kids anymore,

66
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:03,333
so we can't just give in
to our emotions.

67
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:06,267
Aren't you scared?

68
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,933
So many people will be affected.

69
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:12,300
Felma, I can't lie anymore.

70
00:05:12,433 --> 00:05:15,100
I can't hide what
I'm feeling anymore.

71
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:19,700
I've longed for you
for almost two decades,

72
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:23,267
because of one mistake I still
regret to this day.

73
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:29,000
Felma, this is the right time.

74
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:33,833
This is the right time
to make everything right.

75
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,100
That's why I will fight
for this.

76
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:37,300
I will fight for the love I have
for you.

77
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:42,667
You have a wife.

78
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,233
A family.

79
00:05:44,367 --> 00:05:46,833
I know, that's why I'm getting
my marriage annulled.

80
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,267
What about Jeffrey?

81
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,033
And Andrea?

82
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:56,100
They won't accept this.

83
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:58,767
Listen to me.

84
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,567
I will prove to them that
you're the only one...

85
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,633
You're the only one I love.

86
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:08,167
And now, Felma, I'm going
to fulfill my promise

87
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:10,000
to marry you.

88
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:13,600
Felma.

89
00:06:15,033 --> 00:06:18,033
Felma, I won't force you
if you don't want to.

90
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:25,933
Felma, don't you love me
anymore?

91
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,733
Felma, please answer me.

92
00:06:35,867 --> 00:06:39,767
Don't mess with my head, Manuel!

93
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,567
Felma, I'm not messing
with you, I'm just...

94
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:43,033
I don't want to answer that!

95
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:44,433
Why?

96
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:46,400
Because if I do,

97
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:50,733
it's like I'm admitting that
everything Hazel says is true.

98
00:06:50,867 --> 00:06:53,567
That I'm the mistress!

99
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:55,833
Felma, does that mean...

100
00:06:55,967 --> 00:06:56,967
I love you!

101
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:00,700
I still love you!

102
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,567
But I have to fight it.

103
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:09,500
Because you're married to Hazel.

104
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:14,500
In the eyes of people,
in the eyes of the law,

105
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:16,700
I'll still be the mistress.

106
00:07:18,467 --> 00:07:21,333
In the eyes of the law, yes.

107
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:23,433
But in the law of the heart, no.

108
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:29,133
Right here...

109
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:31,167
Here in my heart,
you're the one.

110
00:07:34,167 --> 00:07:35,000
Manuel...

111
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:43,567
not everyone accepts what you
call the law of the heart.

112
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:46,700
Felma, I wasn't able to fight
for you back then.

113
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,100
I've regretted
that my whole life,

114
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:50,167
and I won't let it happen again.

115
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:53,000
That's why I'll fight
for my love for you.

116
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,567
Don't worry, okay?

117
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:01,300
I won't let your
name be tarnished.

118
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:07,167
I will see to it that my
marriage to Hazel gets annulled.

119
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:10,100
And then after that,
I will pursue you.

120
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,667
Felma, I will court you.

121
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,167
Then I'll marry you.

122
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,200
You should!

123
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:29,567
Because no matter what,

124
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:32,333
I will never agree
to be the mistress.

125
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:35,133
Me, too, I won't let that
happen.

126
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:39,167
That's the reason why
Jessica and I are moving out.

127
00:08:40,367 --> 00:08:41,700
Because I don't want us
to be tainted

128
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:44,067
by people's doubt and malice.

129
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:58,000
She's not picking up the phone.

130
00:08:58,133 --> 00:08:59,000
She's not answering my calls.

131
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:01,833
She's not picking up the phone.

132
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,733
Tetay.

133
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:26,600
Mom, where's Dad now?

134
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:28,667
Is he almost here
at the airport?

135
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,167
Can I have my phone?

136
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,933
I'm going to call him.

137
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:41,567
So we can find out
where he is now.

138
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:45,833
Tetay, your dad is
not coming with us.

139
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:47,933
What?

140
00:09:48,067 --> 00:09:49,900
But why?

141
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:55,100
Didn't you say he
planned this vacation?

142
00:09:55,233 --> 00:09:57,400
This is a surprise for me,
right?

143
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:58,867
We're not going on vacation.

144
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,033
We're migrating to Australia.

145
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,767
We're going to your
Aunt Hyacinth.

146
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:07,067
Your dad won't be
coming with us.

147
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,133
What did you say, Mom?

148
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:11,133
My dad won't be coming with us?

149
00:10:11,267 --> 00:10:12,067
We can't do that, Mom.

150
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,500
I want him to be with us.

151
00:10:14,633 --> 00:10:17,033
I don't want to leave him
behind.

152
00:10:17,167 --> 00:10:19,067
I'm sorry, dear.

153
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,700
But it's just going to be
the two of us.

154
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,600
Why?

155
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,167
Sweetie, please pick up.

156
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,900
Sweetie, where are you?

157
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,500
She's not picking up.

158
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:34,233
She's not answering.

159
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:40,633
I thought we'd be
a happy family.

160
00:10:40,767 --> 00:10:44,100
That we'd be complete.

161
00:10:44,233 --> 00:10:47,633
Why are you taking me away
from my dad?

162
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:50,467
Why did you lie to me, Mom?

163
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:53,900
Isn't lying bad?

164
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:56,067
This has been planned
for a long time, sweetie.

165
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,700
What's been planned, Mom?

166
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:01,700
I didn't even know.

167
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:04,733
When I was having problems
with Lance,

168
00:11:04,867 --> 00:11:07,000
I already planned to leave.

169
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:09,900
That's why I talked to Hyacinth.

170
00:11:10,067 --> 00:11:13,767
I didn't know your
dad was coming back.

171
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:17,100
Is that why you
can't commit to him?

172
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:19,267
And you were trying to get him
to go back to Mama Felma

173
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,300
because you already have
other plans?

174
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:27,300
Mom, don't you love him?

175
00:11:27,433 --> 00:11:31,400
Because if you ask me,
Mom, I love him very much.

176
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:32,633
I don't want to leave him.

177
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:34,867
I want to be with him.

178
00:11:37,067 --> 00:11:39,300
Please forgive me, sweetie.

179
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:42,000
But my decision is final.

180
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:44,167
I've dreamed of this
for us for so long.

181
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:47,233
I want us to start over.

182
00:11:47,367 --> 00:11:51,133
How can we start over
if Dad is not coming with us?

183
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:55,067
Give me my phone back.

184
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,433
I want to call Dad.

185
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:58,433
Give me my phone, Mom!

186
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:05,800
Tetay!

187
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:11,333
My daughter left me!

188
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:17,167
Why do they always leave me?

189
00:12:23,267 --> 00:12:26,000
My daughter!

190
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:26,933
<i> Dad!</i>

191
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:28,267
<i> I forgot something!</i>

192
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:29,233
<i> What is it?</i>

193
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:30,767
<i>Did I already say
I love you today?</i>

194
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,267
<i>I thought you forgot
something important.</i>

195
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,700
<i>You said you love me
the moment you woke up.</i>

196
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:34,833
<i> Oh, I didn't forget.</i>

197
00:12:34,967 --> 00:12:36,200
<i> But I still want to say it.</i>

198
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:37,733
<i> I love you, Dad!</i>

199
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:45,633
Where is my daughter?

200
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:50,467
I'm always being left behind!

201
00:12:50,633 --> 00:12:52,967
I'm all alone again!

202
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:02,133
<i>- Let's go.
- Wait, Dad.</i>

203
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:02,867
<i> What is it?</i>

204
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,467
<i> Did I say I love you today?</i>

205
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,567
<i> I don't think so.</i>

206
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:07,600
<i>I didn't get I love you
yesterday either.</i>

207
00:13:07,733 --> 00:13:10,167
<i> You owe me two "I love you".</i>

208
00:13:10,300 --> 00:13:11,133
<i> I love you, Dad!</i>

209
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:13,600
<i> I love you. I love you!</i>

210
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:15,033
<i> Hey, that's three!</i>

211
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:18,233
<i>The other one is for tomorrow,
I might forget again.</i>

212
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:19,500
<i>What? You're becoming forgetful.</i>

213
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:20,300
<i> Come on.</i>

214
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:38,233
Hi, Hazel!

215
00:13:40,667 --> 00:13:42,033
Thank you, Lord.

216
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:44,967
Please guide me on my first day
of work.

217
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:49,800
You know, I'm excited
to start working.

218
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:51,400
It's been a while
since I got a job,

219
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:53,367
and we're working together.

220
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,400
And of course,
I'll meet new friends.

221
00:13:55,567 --> 00:13:57,333
I'm excited to meet them.

222
00:13:57,467 --> 00:13:59,067
What's going on over there?

223
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,833
Nothing, Mom.

224
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:04,033
It's because you're not
observing them.

225
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:05,600
Come on!

226
00:14:05,733 --> 00:14:06,833
Remember?

227
00:14:06,967 --> 00:14:10,633
Your dad might be doing
something with Felma

228
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,033
without your knowledge.

229
00:14:12,167 --> 00:14:14,733
Mom, what do you want me to do?

230
00:14:14,867 --> 00:14:16,233
Do whatever you like,

231
00:14:16,367 --> 00:14:19,300
as long as they don't get back
together.

232
00:14:19,433 --> 00:14:20,667
Let me remind you,

233
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:24,367
you're the one who'll suffer
if that happens.

234
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,000
Mom, what do you want?

235
00:14:31,233 --> 00:14:34,200
What did you mean earlier?

236
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:37,200
That comment about me enjoying
my moments with dad

237
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:39,200
while I still can?

238
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:40,833
What did you mean by that?

239
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:42,800
Jessica, Coleen.

240
00:14:42,933 --> 00:14:45,167
What now?
Are you two fighting again?

241
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:50,667
No, Dad. She's just asking me
a question.

242
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:54,033
Dad, she still doesn't know
that we're leaving.

243
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:01,667
You're leaving, Dad?

244
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:02,433
I'm sorry, sweetie.

245
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:06,533
But we really have to move out.

246
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:10,067
And besides, we all know
that your older siblings

247
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,333
will never come home as long as
Jessica and I are here.

248
00:15:12,467 --> 00:15:13,433
But Dad...

249
00:15:13,567 --> 00:15:16,967
Sweetie, sweetie,
let's not force it anymore.

250
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:18,733
Okay? We've overstayed here
already.

251
00:15:18,867 --> 00:15:20,867
We should've left
a long time ago.

252
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:23,067
But don't worry.

253
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,300
You can still visit us, right?

254
00:15:25,433 --> 00:15:27,100
You can visit every day
if you like.

255
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:45,133
Mon, did Daisy say something
about where they're going?

256
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:48,833
No, did you ask the
other neighbors?

257
00:15:48,967 --> 00:15:49,933
How about Jing?

258
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:50,967
She and Daisy are close.

259
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:52,667
I asked all our neighbors.

260
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:55,933
They don't know where they went.

261
00:15:56,067 --> 00:16:00,033
What about Lyn, your daughter?

262
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,233
She works with Daisy,
doesn't she?

263
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:03,100
Can you please call her and ask?

264
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,000
Wait a minute.

265
00:16:09,467 --> 00:16:11,100
Tetay, sweetie.

266
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:12,333
<i> Dad.</i>

267
00:16:12,467 --> 00:16:14,133
Where are you?
I'm coming to see you.

268
00:16:14,267 --> 00:16:16,567
We're at the airport, Dad.

269
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:17,633
What?

270
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:19,033
Sweetie, where are you going?

271
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:20,433
Why are you at the airport?

272
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:22,033
We're going to Australia.

273
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,167
Sweetie, don't go.

274
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:26,800
Please, don't leave me.

275
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:29,933
Sweetie, don't leave me.

276
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:31,467
No, stay there!

277
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,633
Don't leave!

278
00:16:32,767 --> 00:16:33,467
I'll be there, sweetie.

279
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,100
I'm coming.

280
00:16:36,467 --> 00:16:41,500
Dad, Mom's decision is final.

281
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:50,600
Dad, always remember that
I love you so, so much.

282
00:16:50,733 --> 00:16:56,433
I will try to call you
every day.

283
00:16:56,567 --> 00:16:58,467
<i> To tell you I love you.</i>

284
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:03,567
So I won't owe you
any I love yous.

285
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:06,500
<i>Sweetie, I don't want
just a phone call!</i>

286
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:08,467
Sweetie, I want to see you,

287
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:13,067
hear you, and hold you
while you're saying you love me.

288
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,900
That's what I want.

289
00:17:16,067 --> 00:17:17,667
<i> Don't worry...</i>

290
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,500
I will study hard.

291
00:17:19,633 --> 00:17:22,533
<i> So I can graduate.</i>

292
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,533
And get a job.

293
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:31,433
I will save money
to buy a plane ticket.

294
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:33,633
So I can come back to you.

295
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:36,233
<i> So I can see you again.</i>

296
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:38,933
Sweetie, that will take forever.

297
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:42,300
Sweetie, please stay.

298
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:43,833
I will go to you.

299
00:17:43,967 --> 00:17:45,400
Let me talk to your mom.

300
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:46,900
Give her the phone.

301
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:47,833
Sweetie, please!

302
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,600
Dear, that's enough.

303
00:17:49,733 --> 00:17:51,667
Mom.

304
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:52,267
<i> Daisy!</i>

305
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,033
Let's go.

306
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:54,433
Daisy, please!

307
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:58,200
Daisy, don't take my daughter
away from me!

308
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,433
Daisy!

309
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:16,700
My daughter!

310
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,767
<i>Have you talked to
Attorney Yeban yet?</i>

311
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:41,733
<i>Yes, I gave him
your phone number.</i>

312
00:18:41,867 --> 00:18:43,467
<i> He will talk to you.</i>

313
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,333
Let's go, Dad.

314
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:50,700
We might be late
for your therapy.

315
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:55,467
Dad, you look happy.

316
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:01,267
I just woke up in a
good mood, sweetie.

317
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,667
Let me just finish this, okay?

318
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,433
<i> Thank you, Felma.</i>

319
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:10,067
<i>I'm hoping the annulment
of my marriage to Hazel</i>

320
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:12,333
<i> will be finalized soon.</i>

321
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:16,367
<i>Even if I have to fight her,
I'll do it.</i>

322
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:20,800
<i>So she'll stop getting in
the way of my love for you.</i>

323
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:25,300
<i>Like I said,
I'll make things right.</i>

324
00:19:25,433 --> 00:19:27,300
<i> I'll fight for this.</i>

325
00:19:27,433 --> 00:19:30,167
<i> I have so many plans for us,</i>

326
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:33,567
<i>dreams and promises
I will fulfill.</i>

327
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:37,167
<i>I'll do my best
to rebuild our family.</i>

328
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:39,267
<i>When our children finally
forgive me,</i>

329
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,033
<i>I'll bring back the joy,
the laughter,</i>

330
00:19:41,167 --> 00:19:43,400
<i> and the peace we once had.</i>

331
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:46,167
<i>I'll get my strength back,
Felma.</i>

332
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:49,467
<i>I'll do everything
to walk again.</i>

333
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:52,467
<i>Because it's my dream
to walk you to the altar</i>

334
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,367
<i> without being in a wheelchair.</i>

335
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:10,400
Daydreaming so early
in the morning!

336
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:12,200
I'm just thinking
about something.

337
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,433
What are you thinking about?

338
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:14,767
Share it!

339
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:25,967
Jeff?

340
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:29,133
Sweetie, is there a problem?

341
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:36,833
Daisy and Tetay left me, Mom!

342
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:43,300
Mom, they left me!

343
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,233
I'm all alone again!

344
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:50,200
Why do I always get
left behind, Mom?

345
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:52,100
I talked to my daughter, Mom.

346
00:20:52,233 --> 00:20:53,700
I wanted to see her.

347
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,033
They already left.

348
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:05,400
I always get left behind...

349
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:06,800
Sweetie, calm down.

350
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:11,600
I always get left behind, Mom.

351
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:13,100
Sweetie.

352
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:16,533
Daisy and Tetay are gone.

353
00:21:17,767 --> 00:21:20,000
They don't want me anymore!

354
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,800
Mom, I did everything I could!

355
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:32,733
I did everything
to make things okay.

356
00:21:35,033 --> 00:21:37,100
Tetay...

357
00:21:37,233 --> 00:21:39,733
So we only get a short
while with her.

358
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:44,133
Sweetie, calm down.

359
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:45,200
That's enough.

360
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:51,067
I talked to Col. Sarabia.

361
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,933
I asked him if he knew someone

362
00:21:56,067 --> 00:21:59,200
from the National Immigration
Authority

363
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:01,667
and the Bureau of Overseas
Services.

364
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:05,033
Sweetie, let's go find them.

365
00:22:05,167 --> 00:22:07,833
What if we don't find them?

366
00:22:07,967 --> 00:22:11,833
Don't talk like that.

367
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:15,867
Don't lose hope, sweetie.

368
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:18,233
We're not giving up on Tetay.

369
00:22:18,367 --> 00:22:21,467
If you need to come to Australia
to look for them, do so.

370
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,933
You should do it.

371
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:26,800
You should do it.
I will take care of everything.

372
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:28,300
But for now, sweetie.

373
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:34,100
Can you come home?

374
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:36,933
I don't want you to stay
in the apartment all alone.

375
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:38,833
It's just that you'll
be lonely there.

376
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:40,433
Mom, I don't want to go home.

377
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:42,633
Your ex and his
daughter's there.

378
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:45,133
I won't go home as long
as they're staying there.

379
00:22:45,267 --> 00:22:48,033
Come on, sweetie.

380
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,667
Please.

381
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,567
I won't have peace of mind
when I'm not with you,

382
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:58,333
especially now that you're
carrying so many burdens.

383
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:01,700
You're dealing with so much.

384
00:23:01,833 --> 00:23:03,100
Sweetie, please.

385
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:05,467
Come back home to us.

386
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,400
Lando!

387
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:35,167
What happened to my husband?

388
00:23:35,300 --> 00:23:36,800
Lando!

389
00:23:36,933 --> 00:23:39,667
Where's the doctor?

390
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:42,467
Revive my husband!

391
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,367
Lando!

392
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,267
Ma'am, Ma'am!

393
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:50,167
They tried to revive him,
but he's gone.

394
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:51,400
He's dead.

395
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:52,600
They can't revive him anymore.

396
00:23:52,733 --> 00:23:54,100
I'm so sorry.

397
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:55,500
Lando!

398
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:56,567
Lando!

399
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:57,467
Where is he?

400
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:00,067
Where is my husband?

401
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,733
- Lando!
- Wait a minute...

402
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:03,200
Your husband?

403
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:04,467
Did you say he's your husband?

404
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,667
Yes.

405
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:11,200
Wait, who's the legal wife here?

406
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:15,233
The one married to the patient.

407
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:16,200
It's her.

408
00:24:16,333 --> 00:24:17,167
I am.

409
00:24:19,867 --> 00:24:23,667
Wait a minute, let the legal
wife have a moment with him.

410
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,600
Come on, let's go outside.

411
00:24:25,733 --> 00:24:27,767
No, it's okay.

412
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:30,367
She also has the right to
be here with my husband.

413
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:37,433
Lando! What happened to you?

414
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:45,600
So the woman you're trying
to comfort is the mistress?

415
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:48,767
She and the legal wife
get along fine.

416
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:52,300
So it's okay to share.

417
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:53,833
It's not okay with me.

418
00:24:54,933 --> 00:24:57,167
That kind of setup will
never be okay with me.

419
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:58,500
No way.

420
00:25:10,867 --> 00:25:12,567
Dad, let's celebrate.

421
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:18,200
The therapist is glad with
your big improvement.

422
00:25:18,333 --> 00:25:21,000
I'll treat you to coffee, Dad.
Okay?

423
00:25:21,133 --> 00:25:22,767
All right, I like that, sweetie.

424
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,167
Go ahead, get the coffee.

425
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:29,167
Okay, Dad.

426
00:25:33,867 --> 00:25:34,900
Hello, Attorney?

427
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:42,833
Yes, it's about Hazel's abuse,
both physical and emotional.

428
00:25:42,967 --> 00:25:44,633
That's what I'll be using
as grounds

429
00:25:44,767 --> 00:25:47,633
for the case I'm filing
against her.

430
00:25:47,767 --> 00:25:53,367
What exactly is
psychological incapacity?

431
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:54,867
Yes.

432
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,600
Yes, Attorney.

433
00:25:56,733 --> 00:25:59,200
I'm determined.

434
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:01,267
All right then.

435
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:02,000
Okay.

436
00:26:04,333 --> 00:26:06,600
Thank you so much, Attorney.

437
00:26:10,667 --> 00:26:11,467
Are you okay?

438
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:12,667
Mom, what happened?

439
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,900
Your dad is filing for an
annulment of our marriage.

440
00:26:15,033 --> 00:26:16,233
Help me, sweetie.

441
00:26:16,367 --> 00:26:19,433
Are you sure he's coming?

442
00:26:19,567 --> 00:26:20,400
Jeffrey!

443
00:26:20,533 --> 00:26:21,867
I miss you!

444
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,033
Jeffrey...

445
00:26:23,167 --> 00:26:26,233
Thank you for coming back,
even though Dad is here.

446
00:26:26,367 --> 00:26:28,267
I didn't really have
anywhere to go.

447
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:30,900
I just hope we can go back
to how things were before.

448
00:26:31,033 --> 00:26:32,633
I miss us.

449
00:26:32,767 --> 00:26:35,100
If Felma and Manuel
get back together,

450
00:26:35,233 --> 00:26:36,900
you'll lose your place
in his life.

451
00:26:37,033 --> 00:26:39,233
He will never abandon me,
no matter what happens.

452
00:26:39,367 --> 00:26:41,367
Do you think he'll still
fight for you

453
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:43,833
when he finds out that you're
not his biological daughter?
